Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C.

Heat a glug of @oil{glug} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Fry, turning frequently until the chicken is browned on the outside, ~{3-5%minutes}.

While the chicken is cooking, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can} in a #colander{}, put half of them in a #bowl{} and roughly mash. Add the remaining whole beans to the bowl and combine.

Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{150%g}(drained and rinsed) in a #sieve{}.

Once the chicken is browned, add the shallot to the pan. Fry, stirring frequently until the shallot has softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @Mexican style spice mix{1} and sweetcorn, cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: Add less spice if you don't like heat.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1}, @water{200%ml} (see ingredient list for amount), @chicken stock powder{1} and black beans (whole and mashed).

Add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, @pepper{pinch} and @?sugar{pinch} (if you have some).

Bring to the boil, stirring continuously, then reduce the heat to medium.

Cover the pan with a #lid{} or some #foil{} and simmer until the mixture is thick and the chicken is cooked, ~{6-8%minutes}, stirring every 2 mins or so.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the stew cooks, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}(grated).

Cut each @ciabatta{1} in half as though you're making a sandwich. Place on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Bake for ~{5%minutes}.

Once the stew is cooked, stir in the @baby spinach{125%g} a handful at a time until wilted.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if needed.

Remove from the heat, taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Serve in #bowls{} with the cheddar scattered on top and the ciabatta alongside. Enjoy!